					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">DarkMoe wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">So, what I did now, is to ignore the fine x scroll, and then move shift all pixels to the left using the fine X scroll value.</div><br />It turns out that's exactly what the PPU actually does. Fine X scroll has absolutely nothing to do with how tiles are fetched. The PPU has a set of shift registers used as a variable delay line to move the background 8-1 pixels to the right for fine X scroll values of 0-7.</div>

